The paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as question-answering, sentiment analysis, and language modeling, which are typically covered under the arXiv sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Machine Learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper also explores the use of BERT, a popular language model, which falls under the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a novel post-training approach, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of Computation and Complexity (cs.CC).
